<section class="explainer">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div>
        <h3>What is technical insulation?</h3>
        <p><strong>Technical insulation</strong> is the umbrella discipline that insulates equipment, building services and structural elements — thermal, acoustic and fire-rated insulation on pipes, conduits, ducts, walls and load-bearing structure.</p>
        <p>Within technical insulation, fire protection is a specialty of its own: it prevents fire and smoke from spreading between rooms where pipes, cables and ducts pass through fire-rated walls and floors.</p>
        <div class="bullet-row">
          <span class="chip blue">Thermal</span>
          <span class="chip blue">Acoustic</span>
          <span class="chip">Fire insulation</span>
          <span class="chip">Fire sealing</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3>Our services</h3>
        <p>We offer <strong>complete technical insulation</strong> for buildings — fire protection, pipe insulation and ventilation insulation, both indoor and outdoor.</p>
        <p>The work falls into four main areas:</p>
        <div class="bullet-row">
          <span class="chip">Fire sealing</span>
          <span class="chip">Fireproofing</span>
          <span class="chip">Pipe insulation</span>
          <span class="chip">Ventilation insulation</span>
        </div>
        <p>We use certified systems from Roxtec, Hilti, Promat, 3M, <strong>Isogenopak</strong> and <strong>WrapTec</strong> — we plan the job, install it and deliver an inspection report and project handover report to the owner.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

